The past year has been filled with notable achievements in our programs and projects in

December 2023
Made infrastructure improvements to the casa comunal in El Presidio Liberado and to the
Isla de Monte Cristo school.
Funded the Womens Network of Morazans empowering program for girls and young
women, providing sexual and reproductive health education from a womens rights
perspective.
These achievements have been possible thanks to the active participation of our partners in
El Salvador, the untiring dedication of our team and, above all, to the trust and support of
persons like you.
Our work this year has also brought us new and
significant challenges, the result of an ongoing
economic crisis and increasingly erratic weather
patterns linked to climate change. The Bajo Lempa
region, especially the smaller communities where
we have begun to work, have been hard hit by both
recurrent flooding and extended droughts, leading
to the loss of animals and crops.

Of the 53 families that reside there, nearly half reported monthly incomes of less than $100 - a
situation of extreme poverty. Over 60% of families surveyed have reduced the quantity of food
they consume daily, and more than one-third have eliminated one of their daily meals. The
situation is surely similar in other small communities including our partners Los Calix and La
Canoita, where poverty is clearly evident.

a key objective for Voices in 2024 is
to provide those families most in need with
technical assistance and material resources so that
they can establish climate-resilient family gardens.
By producing fresh and nutritious food using
sustainable cultivation methods that enrich the
soil and plant varieties that are resistant to
flooding and drought, food security will be
enhanced in these communities.
